    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="919"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d919">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/13384.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of War</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 23, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your letter of September 21 in regard to the exaction of further payments
                    [etc.]</p>
                <pb facs="0720" n="604" xml:id="pg_604"/>
                <p>In reply I have the honor to enclose herewith, for your information, a copy of a
                    telegram which the Department despatched on September 22 to the Brazilian
                    Minister at Mexico City in connection with these matters.</p>
                <p>The Department will be glad to take up the other matters mentioned in your letter
                    when a reply is received from the Brazilian Minister.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <p>For the Secretary of State,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
